 Settlement of German Jews]], London\n* [[Central Committee for Refugees from Germany]], Prague\n* Centre de recherches de solutions au probl\u00e8me juif, Paris\n* Comit\u00e9 d'aide et d'assistance aux victimes de l'anti-semitisme en Allemagne, Brussels\n* Comite for Bijzondere Joodsche Belangen, Amsterdam\n* Comit\u00e9 international pour le placement des intellectuels r\u00e9fugi\u00e9s, Geneva\n* Comit\u00e9 pour la d\u00e9fense des droits des Isra\u00e9lites en Europe centrale et orientale, Paris\n* [[Committee of Aid for German Jews]], London\n* [[Council for German Jewry]], London\n* [[Emigration Advisory Committee]], London\n* F\u00e9d\u00e9ration des \u00e9migr\u00e9s d'Autriche, Paris\n* F\u00e9d\u00e9ration internationale des \u00e9migr\u00e9s d'Allemagne, Paris\n* ''[[Freeland League|Freeland]]'' Association, London\n* German Committee of the Quaker [[Society of Friends]], London\n* [[HIAS|HICEM]], Paris<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.yadvashem.org/odot_pdf/Microsoft%20Word%20-%206368.pdf|title=History of HICEM|publisher=|accessdate=June 1, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[International Christian Committee for Non-Aryans]], London\n* [[Socialist and Labour International|Internationale ouvri\u00e8re et socialiste]], Paris and Brussels\n* [[Jewish Agency for Israel|Jewish Agency for Palestine]], London\n* The Joint Foreign Committee of the [[Board of Deputies of British Jews]] and the [[Anglo-Jewish Association]], London\n* Komitee f\u00fcr die Entwicklung der grossen j\u00fcdischen Kolonisation, Z\u00fcrich\n* [[League of Nations Union]], London\n* [[New Zionist Organization]], London\n* [[World ORT|ORT]], Paris\n* [[Chatham House|Royal Institute of International Affairs]], London\n* Schweizer Hilfszentrum f\u00fcr Fl\u00fcchtlinge, Basel\n* Service international de migration, Geneva\n* Service universitaire international, Geneva\n* Soci\u00e9t\u00e9 d'\u00e9migration et de colonisation juive ''Emcol'', Paris\n* [[Society for the Protection of Sciences and Studies]], London\n* Union des Soci\u00e9t\u00e9s OSE, Paris\n* [[World Jewish Congress]], Paris\n\n===Press===\nThe international press was represented by about two hundred journalists, chiefly the League of Nations correspondents of the leading daily and weekly newspapers and news agencies.<ref>A list of the papers and agencies and their reporters was published by [[Hans Habe]], present at the Conference as a foreign correspondent of the ''Prager Tagblatt'' ([[Prague]] Daily), as an appendix to his novel ''Die Mission'' (''[[The Mission (novel)|The Mission]]'', 1965, first published in Great Britain by George G. Harrap & Co. Limited in 1966, re-published by Panther Books Ltd, book number 2231, in 1967).</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Kristallnacht]] (November 9, 1938)\n* [[The Holocaust]]\n* [[Bermuda Conference]]\n* [[British Mandate for Palestine (legal instrument)|British Mandate of Palestine]]\n* [[White Paper of 1939]]\n* [[SS St. Louis|SS ''St. Louis'']]\n* [[SS Navemar]]\n* [[International response to the Holocaust]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/Holocaust/evian.html Decisions Taken at the \u00c9vian Conference]\n* [http://www1.yadvashem.org/yv/en/exhibitions/this_month/july/02.asp?WT.mc_id=wiki The \u00c9vian Conference] on the [[Yad Vashem]] website\n* [https://www.transatlantikblog.de/2018/02/04/konferenz-von-evian-1938-teil-1/ Original contemporary news from the english daily ''Palestine Post'']\n* [http://www.sosuamuseum.org Sos\u00faa Virtual Museum    Living memorial to the Sos\u00faa settlers]\n\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2012}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Evian}}\n[[Category:Jewish emigration from Nazi Germany]]\n[[Category:International response during the Holocaust]]\n[[Category:Diplomatic conferences in France]]\n[[Category:International conferences in France]]\n[[Category:20th-century diplomatic conferences]]\n[[Category:1938 conferences]]\n[[Category:1938 in international relations]]\n[[Category:1938 in France]]\n[[Category:The Holocaust and the United States]]\n[[Category:July 1938 events]]\n", "name_user": "Chesdovi", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%89vian_Conference"}
{"title_page": "Green Party (Norway)", "text_new": "{{Infobox political party\n| name = Green Party\n| colorcode = {{Green Party (Norway)/meta/color}}\n| spokesperson = [[Une Aina Bastholm]]<br />[[Arild Hermstad]]\n| foundation = 29 October 1988\n| ideology = [[Green politics]]<ref name=\"Nordsieck\">{{cite web|url=http://www.parties-and-elections.eu/norway.html|title=Norway|last=Nordsieck|first=Wolfram|date=2017|website=Parties and Elections in Europe|accessdate=13 August 2018}}</ref>\n| headquarters = [[Oslo]]\n| international = [[Global Greens]]\n| website = [http://www.mdg.no/ www.mdg.no]\n| country = Norway\n| native_name = Milj\u00f8partiet De Gr\u00f8nne\n| logo = Milj\u00f8partiet de Gr\u00f8nne logo.svg\n| logo_size = 200px\n| european = [[European Green Party]]\n| youth_wing = [[Young Greens of Norway]]\n| position = [[Centre-left politics|Centre-left]]<ref name=\"uio\">{{cite news|author=Jupsk\u00e5s, Anders Ravik |url=http://www.sv.uio.no/isv/forskning/aktuelt/blogg/ta-politika/2011/de-gronne.html |title=En mild gr\u00f8nn vind i norske byer: MDGs lokale gjennombrudd |language=Norwegian |publisher=UiO: Institutt for statsvitenskap (ISV): Det samfunnsvitenskapelige fakultet |date=14 September 2011|quote=\"I mine unders\u00f8kelser av partienes landsm\u00f8tedelegater (de som vedtar partiets politikk) kommer det frem at partiet i all hovedsak plasserer seg p\u00e5 \u00abvenstresiden\u00bb i norsk politikk.\"}}</ref><ref name=\"vox\">{{cite news|author=Arnesen, Sveinung|title=Ligger Milj\u00f8partiet De Gr\u00f8nne i sentrum eller til venstre?|url=http://voxpublica.no/2015/03/ligger-miljopartiet-de-gronne-i-sentrum-eller-til-venstre/|work=Vox Publica|date=9 March 2015|language=Norwegian|quote=\"Data fra Norsk medborgerpanel viser at velgerne plasserer partiet til venstre for sentrum.\"}}</ref>\n| colours = Green\n| membership_year = 2019\n| membership = {{Increase}} 9,963<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dagbladet.no/nyheter/doblet-medlemstallene-pa-to-ar/72001690 | editor=[[Dagbladet]] | title= Doblet medlemstallene p\u00e5 to \u00e5r| date= 7 January 2020 | accessdate= 20 February 2020 | lang=no-NB}}</ref>\n| seats1_title = [[Storting]]\n| seats1 = {{Composition bar|1|169|hex={{Green Party (Norway)/meta/color}}}}\n| seats2_title = [[County council (Norway)|County Councils]]\n| seats2 = {{Composition bar|36|574|hex={{Green Party (Norway)/meta/color}}}}\n| seats3_title = [[Municipal council (Norway)|Municipal Councils]]\n| seats3 = {{Composition bar|310|9344|hex={{Green Party (Norway)/meta/color}}}}\n}}\n{{Green politics sidebar}}\nThe '''Green Party''' ({{lang-nb|Milj\u00f8partiet De Gr\u00f8nne}}, {{lang-nn|Milj\u00f8partiet Dei Gr\u00f8ne}}, literally \"Environment Party The Greens\") is a [[green politics|green]]<ref name=\"Nordsieck\"/> [[List of political parties in Norway|political party]] in [[Norway]]. The party holds one seat in the [[Storting|Parliament of Norway]] (gaining 2.8% in the [[2013 Norwegian parliamentary election|2013 elections]]) and also has representation in [[Municipalities of Norway|municipal]] councils and [[County council (Norway)|county councils]] (gaining 4.2% in the [[2015 Norwegian local elections|2015 elections]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.regjeringen.no/krd/html/valg2011/bf5.html |title=Landsoversikt per parti |language=Norwegian |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110924171401/http://www.regjeringen.no/krd/html/valg2011/bf5.html |archivedate=2011-09-24 }}</ref> The Green Party advocates [[green politics]], and has been described as centre-left by academics and voters.<ref name=\"uio\"/><ref name=\"vox\"/> The party itself claims distance to the two dominant right-wing and left-wing political blocs, jointly denominated as \"the fossil block\".<ref>{{cite web |author=Av Milj\u00f8partiet De Gr\u00f8nne |url=http://www.mdg.no/nyheter/verken-rod-eller-bla-men-gronn-2/ |title=Verken r\u00f8d eller bl\u00e5, men gr\u00f8nn |publisher=Milj\u00f8partiet De Gr\u00f8nne |date=21 May 2013 |accessdate=2013-11-21 |language=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141016131307/http://www.mdg.no/nyheter/verken-rod-eller-bla-men-gronn-2/ |archive-date=16 October 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nThe Green Party is a member of the [[European Green Party]] and the [[Global Greens]], and was founded with the [[Alliance '90/The Greens|German Greens]] as its stated model.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogg.bt.no/preik/2013/01/16/de-gronne-banker-pa-2/#.VDr5Mrtvt2Y|title=De Gr\u00f8nne banker p\u00e5  -  Preik|work=bt.no|accessdate=15 October 2016}}</ref> It maintains close ties to other Green parties including the German Greens and the [[Green Party (Sweden)|Swedish Greens]].\n\n==History==\nThe process of forming a new national green party in Norway was initiated in December 1984, with the official launch in 1988.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkunne.no/default.aspx?menu=272&id=7222 |title=Milj\u00f8partiet Dei Gr\u00f8ne |publisher=Allkunne |date= |accessdate=2013-11-21 |language=no}}</ref> Among the pioneers were the late philosopher [[Arne N\u00e6ss]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2009/jan/15/obituary-arne-naess |work=The Guardian |first=Walter |last=Schwarz |title=Obituary: Arne N\u00e6ss |date=15 January 2009}}</ref> peace researcher [[Johan Galtung]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://nordlyspuls.no/-/bulletin/print/190722_johan-galtung-mottok-aeresmedlemskap?ref=mst |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120712094447/http://nordlyspuls.no/-/bulletin/print/190722_johan-galtung-mottok-aeresmedlemskap?ref=mst |url-status=dead |archive-date=2012-07-12 |title=Nordlys : Johan Galtung mottok \u00e6resmedlemskap |publisher=Nordlyspuls.no |accessdate=2013-11-21 |language=no }}</ref> and the philosopher [[Sigmund Kval\u00f8y Setreng]].\n\nIn the local elections between 1991 and 2009 the Green Party had 6 - 8 representatives elected each time. In the national elections the party never exceeded 0.5% support.\n\nSince 2005, the Greens have seen a significant membership rise, with the new members coming from a wide variety of other parties, including the seven established parliamentary parties.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tv2.no/nyheter/politisk/de-groennes-historie-3976426.html |title=De Gr\u00f8nnes historie - Siste nytt - innenriks, utenriks |publisher=Tv2.no |date=2013-05-24 |accessdate=2013-11-21 |language=no}}</ref>\n\nIn the [[2011 Norwegian local elections|municipal elections of 2011]], the party saw its first local breakthrough, having garnered close to 22,000 votes on a national basis. Two years later, during the campaign for the [[2013 Norwegian parliamentary election|2013 general election]], the party saw a significant rise in support in the opinion polls. The Greens were widely expected to gain parliamentary representation to some extent.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogg.tv2.no/tom-hetland/2013/08/16/blir-dei-grone-arets-sensasjon/ |title=Blir Dei Gr\u00f8ne \u00e5rets sensasjon? |author=Tom Hetland |publisher=TV 2 |date=2013-08-16 |accessdate=2013-11-21 |language=no}}</ref> In the election, the Greens gathered over 79,000 votes, making them the 8th biggest party in the country. This vote count translates to 2.8 percent of the vote. [[Rasmus Hansson]], the party's top candidate from [[Oslo]] was elected to parliament, becoming the first ever Green MP.<ref>MP.http://www.nettavisen.no/politikk/article3675551.ece</ref>\n\nIn the local elections of 2015 the Green Party overtook the 4% nationally for the first time in its history and got the third place in Oslo.\n\n==Ideology==\nThe Green Party is one of the global ecologist and environmentalist political parties and movements.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mdg.no/om-oss/ |title=Om oss |publisher=Milj\u00f8partiet De Gr\u00f8nne |language=no |date= |accessdate=2013-11-21}}</ref> As a member of the pan-European [[European Green Party]], the Norwegian Greens subscribe to social progressivism and social justice.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mdg.no/politikk/politikk-fra-a-a/velferd-og-arbeidsliv/ |title=Velferd og arbeidsliv |publisher=Milj\u00f8partiet De Gr\u00f8nne |language=no |accessdate=2013-11-21 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20131109143543/http://www.mdg.no/politikk/politikk-fra-a-a/velferd-og-arbeidsliv/ |archivedate=2013-11-09 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mdg.no/politikk/politikk-fra-a-a/utvikling-og-bistand/ |title=Utvikling og bistand |publisher=Milj\u00f8partiet De Gr\u00f8nne |language=no |date= |accessdate=2013-11-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131109152016/http://www.mdg.no/politikk/politikk-fra-a-a/utvikling-og-bistand/ |archive-date=2013-11-09 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The main focus of the party is environmental protection and ecological sustainability. The party seeks to introduce a tax on wasteful consumption, and to reorganise the food industry. The Greens have also pledged support for a reform in the agrarian industry, increasing the production of organic crops and strengthening the eco-friendly agricultural sector.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mdg.no/politikk/politikk-fra-a-a/tema-3-2/ |title=Livskvalitet &#124; Milj\u00f8partiet De Gr\u00f8nne |publisher=Mdg.no |accessdate=2013-11-21 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131109151801/http://www.mdg.no/politikk/politikk-fra-a-a/tema-3-2/ |archivedate=2013-11-09 }}</ref>\n\nThe Green party seeks to reduce the Norwegian petroleum extraction in order to counteract serious [[climate change]]. The proposal is to stop extraction by 2033.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mdg.no/politikk/politikk-fra-a-a/fornybar-fremtid/ |title=Fornybar fremtid |publisher=Milj\u00f8partiet De Gr\u00f8nne |language=no |date= |accessdate=2013-11-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150517222736/https://www.mdg.no/politikk/politikk-fra-a-a/fornybar-fremtid/ |archive-date=2015-05-17 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nThe party does not have a leader in the traditional sense, rather it is led by the national executive committee which consists of seven persons. Among the board members, two persons (currently [[Arild Hermstad]] and [[Une Aina Bastholm]]), act as national spokespersons for the party. All party representatives are elected during the annual party convention.\n\n==Election results==\n[[File:MDG Valgvake 2013 (10024177254).jpg|thumb|The party's member of [[Parliament of Norway|Parliament]], [[Rasmus Hansson]], being interviewed by the [[Norwegian Broadcasting Corporation]] on the [[2013 Norwegian parliamentary election|2013 election night]]]]\n[[File:MDG Valgvake 2013 (10024221645).jpg|thumb|Former national spokeswoman [[Hanna Marcussen]]]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ [[Storting]] elections\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Date\n! colspan=\"3\"| Votes\n! colspan=\"2\"| Seats\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Position\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Size\n|-\n! #\n! %\n! \u00b1\n! \u00b1\n|-\n! [[1989 Norwegian parliamentary election|1989]]\n| 10,136\n| 0.4%\n| + 0.4\n| {{Composition bar|0|165|#67962e}}\n| {{steady}} 0\n| N/A\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 9th\n|-\n! [[1993 Norwegian parliamentary election|1993]]\n| 3,054\n| 0.1%\n| - 0.3\n| {{Composition bar|0|165|#67962e}}\n| {{steady}} 0\n| N/A\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 12th\n|-\n! [[1997 Norwegian parliamentary election|1997]]\n| 5,884\n| 0.2%\n| + 0.1\n| {{Composition bar|0|165|#67962e}}\n| {{steady}} 0\n| N/A\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 11th\n|-\n! [[2001 Norwegian parliamentary election|2001]]\n| 3,785\n| 0.2%\n| + 0.0\n| {{Composition bar|0|165|#67962e}}\n| {{steady}} 0\n| N/A\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 13th\n|-\n! [[2005 Norwegian parliamentary election|2005]]\n| 3,652\n| 0.1%\n| - 0.1\n| {{Composition bar|0|169|#67962e}}\n| {{steady}} 0\n| N/A\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 12th\n|-\n! [[2009 Norwegian parliamentary election|2009]]\n| 9,286\n| 0.3%\n| + 0.2\n| {{Composition bar|0|169|#67962e}}\n| {{steady}} 0\n| N/A\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 10th\n|-\n! [[2013 Norwegian parliamentary election|2013]]\n| 79,152\n| 2.8%\n| + 2.5\n| {{Composition bar|1|169|#67962e}}\n| {{increase}} 1\n| style=\"background:#fcc;\"| Opposition\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 8th\n|-\n! [[2017 Norwegian parliamentary election|2017]]\n| 94,427\n| 3.2%\n| + 0.4\n| {{Composition bar|1|169|#67962e}}\n| {{steady}} 0\n| style=\"background:#fcc;\"| Opposition\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 8th\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Green party]]\n* [[Green politics]]\n* [[List of environmental organizations]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Milj\u00f8partiet De Gr\u00f8nne}}\n*{{in lang|no}} [http://www.mdg.no/ Official site]\n\n{{Norwegian political parties}}\n{{Green parties}}\n\n[[Category:Green parties in Europe]]\n[[Category:1988 establishments in Norway]]\n[[Category:European Green Party]]\n[[Category:Environmental organisations based in Norway]]\n[[Category:Political parties established in 1988]]\n[[Category:Global Greens member parties]]\n[[Category:Political parties in Norway]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox political party\n| name = Green Party\n| colorcode = {{Green Party (Norway)/meta/color}}\n| spokesperson = [[Une Aina Bastholm]]<br />[[Arild Hermstad]]\n| foundation = 29 October 1988\n| ideology = [[Green politics]]<ref name=\"Nordsieck\">{{cite web|url=http://www.parties-and-elections.eu/norway.html|title=Norway|last=Nordsieck|first=Wolfram|date=2017|website=Parties and Elections in Europe|accessdate=13 August 2018}}</ref>\n| headquarters = [[Oslo]]\n| international = [[Global Greens]]\n| website = [http://www.mdg.no/ www.mdg.no]\n| country = Norway\n| native_name = Milj\u00f8partiet De Gr\u00f8nne\n| logo = Milj\u00f8partiet de Gr\u00f8nne logo.svg\n| logo_size = 200px\n| european = [[European Green Party]]\n| youth_wing = [[Young Greens of Norway]]\n| position = [[Centre-left politics|Centre-left]]<ref name=\"uio\">{{cite news|author=Jupsk\u00e5s, Anders Ravik |url=http://www.sv.uio.no/isv/forskning/aktuelt/blogg/ta-politika/2011/de-gronne.html |title=En mild gr\u00f8nn vind i norske byer: MDGs lokale gjennombrudd |language=Norwegian |publisher=UiO: Institutt for statsvitenskap (ISV): Det samfunnsvitenskapelige fakultet |date=14 September 2011|quote=\"I mine unders\u00f8kelser av partienes landsm\u00f8tedelegater (de som vedtar partiets politikk) kommer det frem at partiet i all hovedsak plasserer seg p\u00e5 \u00abvenstresiden\u00bb i norsk politikk.\"}}</ref><ref name=\"vox\">{{cite news|author=Arnesen, Sveinung|title=Ligger Milj\u00f8partiet De Gr\u00f8nne i sentrum eller til venstre?|url=http://voxpublica.no/2015/03/ligger-miljopartiet-de-gronne-i-sentrum-eller-til-venstre/|work=Vox Publica|date=9 March 2015|language=Norwegian|quote=\"Data fra Norsk medborgerpanel viser at velgerne plasserer partiet til venstre for sentrum.\"}}</ref>\n| colours = Green\n| membership_year = 2019\n| membership = {{Increase}} 9,963<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dagbladet.no/nyheter/doblet-medlemstallene-pa-to-ar/72001690 | editor=[[Dagbladet]] | title= Doblet medlemstallene p\u00e5 to \u00e5r| date= 7 January 2020 | accessdate= 20 February 2020 | lang=no-NB}}</ref>\n| seats1_title = [[Storting]]\n| seats1 = {{Composition bar|1|169|hex={{Green Party (Norway)/meta/color}}}}\n| seats2_title = [[County council (Norway)|County Councils]]\n| seats2 = {{Composition bar|36|574|hex={{Green Party (Norway)/meta/color}}}}\n| seats3_title = [[Municipal council (Norway)|Municipal Councils]]\n| seats3 = {{Composition bar|310|9344|hex={{Green Party (Norway)/meta/color}}}}\n}}\n{{Green politics sidebar}}\nThe '''Green Party''' ({{lang-nb|Milj\u00f8partiet De Gr\u00f8nne}}, {{lang-nn|Milj\u00f8partiet Dei Gr\u00f8ne}}, {{lang-sme|Birasbellodat Ruon\u00e1t}}, literally \"Environment Party The Greens\") is a [[green politics|green]]<ref name=\"Nordsieck\"/> [[List of political parties in Norway|political party]] in [[Norway]]. The party holds one seat in the [[Storting|Parliament of Norway]] (gaining 2.8% in the [[2013 Norwegian parliamentary election|2013 elections]]) and also has representation in [[Municipalities of Norway|municipal]] councils and [[County council (Norway)|county councils]] (gaining 4.2% in the [[2015 Norwegian local elections|2015 elections]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.regjeringen.no/krd/html/valg2011/bf5.html |title=Landsoversikt per parti |language=Norwegian |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110924171401/http://www.regjeringen.no/krd/html/valg2011/bf5.html |archivedate=2011-09-24 }}</ref> The Green Party advocates [[green politics]], and has been described as centre-left by academics and voters.<ref name=\"uio\"/><ref name=\"vox\"/> The party itself claims distance to the two dominant right-wing and left-wing political blocs, jointly denominated as \"the fossil block\".<ref>{{cite web |author=Av Milj\u00f8partiet De Gr\u00f8nne |url=http://www.mdg.no/nyheter/verken-rod-eller-bla-men-gronn-2/ |title=Verken r\u00f8d eller bl\u00e5, men gr\u00f8nn |publisher=Milj\u00f8partiet De Gr\u00f8nne |date=21 May 2013 |accessdate=2013-11-21 |language=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141016131307/http://www.mdg.no/nyheter/verken-rod-eller-bla-men-gronn-2/ |archive-date=16 October 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nThe Green Party is a member of the [[European Green Party]] and the [[Global Greens]], and was founded with the [[Alliance '90/The Greens|German Greens]] as its stated model.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogg.bt.no/preik/2013/01/16/de-gronne-banker-pa-2/#.VDr5Mrtvt2Y|title=De Gr\u00f8nne banker p\u00e5  -  Preik|work=bt.no|accessdate=15 October 2016}}</ref> It maintains close ties to other Green parties including the German Greens and the [[Green Party (Sweden)|Swedish Greens]].\n\n==History==\nThe process of forming a new national green party in Norway was initiated in December 1984, with the official launch in 1988.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkunne.no/default.aspx?menu=272&id=7222 |title=Milj\u00f8partiet Dei Gr\u00f8ne |publisher=Allkunne |date= |accessdate=2013-11-21 |language=no}}</ref> Among the pioneers were the late philosopher [[Arne N\u00e6ss]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2009/jan/15/obituary-arne-naess |work=The Guardian |first=Walter |last=Schwarz |title=Obituary: Arne N\u00e6ss |date=15 January 2009}}</ref> peace researcher [[Johan Galtung]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://nordlyspuls.no/-/bulletin/print/190722_johan-galtung-mottok-aeresmedlemskap?ref=mst |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120712094447/http://nordlyspuls.no/-/bulletin/print/190722_johan-galtung-mottok-aeresmedlemskap?ref=mst |url-status=dead |archive-date=2012-07-12 |title=Nordlys : Johan Galtung mottok \u00e6resmedlemskap |publisher=Nordlyspuls.no |accessdate=2013-11-21 |language=no }}</ref> and the philosopher [[Sigmund Kval\u00f8y Setreng]].\n\nIn the local elections between 1991 and 2009 the Green Party had 6 - 8 representatives elected each time. In the national elections the party never exceeded 0.5% support.\n\nSince 2005, the Greens have seen a significant membership rise, with the new members coming from a wide variety of other parties, including the seven established parliamentary parties.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tv2.no/nyheter/politisk/de-groennes-historie-3976426.html |title=De Gr\u00f8nnes historie - Siste nytt - innenriks, utenriks |publisher=Tv2.no |date=2013-05-24 |accessdate=2013-11-21 |language=no}}</ref>\n\nIn the [[2011 Norwegian local elections|municipal elections of 2011]], the party saw its first local breakthrough, having garnered close to 22,000 votes on a national basis. Two years later, during the campaign for the [[2013 Norwegian parliamentary election|2013 general election]], the party saw a significant rise in support in the opinion polls. The Greens were widely expected to gain parliamentary representation to some extent.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogg.tv2.no/tom-hetland/2013/08/16/blir-dei-grone-arets-sensasjon/ |title=Blir Dei Gr\u00f8ne \u00e5rets sensasjon? |author=Tom Hetland |publisher=TV 2 |date=2013-08-16 |accessdate=2013-11-21 |language=no}}</ref> In the election, the Greens gathered over 79,000 votes, making them the 8th biggest party in the country. This vote count translates to 2.8 percent of the vote. [[Rasmus Hansson]], the party's top candidate from [[Oslo]] was elected to parliament, becoming the first ever Green MP.<ref>MP.http://www.nettavisen.no/politikk/article3675551.ece</ref>\n\nIn the local elections of 2015 the Green Party overtook the 4% nationally for the first time in its history and got the third place in Oslo.\n\n==Ideology==\nThe Green Party is one of the global ecologist and environmentalist political parties and movements.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mdg.no/om-oss/ |title=Om oss |publisher=Milj\u00f8partiet De Gr\u00f8nne |language=no |date= |accessdate=2013-11-21}}</ref> As a member of the pan-European [[European Green Party]], the Norwegian Greens subscribe to social progressivism and social justice.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mdg.no/politikk/politikk-fra-a-a/velferd-og-arbeidsliv/ |title=Velferd og arbeidsliv |publisher=Milj\u00f8partiet De Gr\u00f8nne |language=no |accessdate=2013-11-21 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20131109143543/http://www.mdg.no/politikk/politikk-fra-a-a/velferd-og-arbeidsliv/ |archivedate=2013-11-09 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mdg.no/politikk/politikk-fra-a-a/utvikling-og-bistand/ |title=Utvikling og bistand |publisher=Milj\u00f8partiet De Gr\u00f8nne |language=no |date= |accessdate=2013-11-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131109152016/http://www.mdg.no/politikk/politikk-fra-a-a/utvikling-og-bistand/ |archive-date=2013-11-09 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The main focus of the party is environmental protection and ecological sustainability. The party seeks to introduce a tax on wasteful consumption, and to reorganise the food industry. The Greens have also pledged support for a reform in the agrarian industry, increasing the production of organic crops and strengthening the eco-friendly agricultural sector.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mdg.no/politikk/politikk-fra-a-a/tema-3-2/ |title=Livskvalitet &#124; Milj\u00f8partiet De Gr\u00f8nne |publisher=Mdg.no |accessdate=2013-11-21 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131109151801/http://www.mdg.no/politikk/politikk-fra-a-a/tema-3-2/ |archivedate=2013-11-09 }}</ref>\n\nThe Green party seeks to reduce the Norwegian petroleum extraction in order to counteract serious [[climate change]]. The proposal is to stop extraction by 2033.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mdg.no/politikk/politikk-fra-a-a/fornybar-fremtid/ |title=Fornybar fremtid |publisher=Milj\u00f8partiet De Gr\u00f8nne |language=no |date= |accessdate=2013-11-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150517222736/https://www.mdg.no/politikk/politikk-fra-a-a/fornybar-fremtid/ |archive-date=2015-05-17 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nThe party does not have a leader in the traditional sense, rather it is led by the national executive committee which consists of seven persons. Among the board members, two persons (currently [[Arild Hermstad]] and [[Une Aina Bastholm]]), act as national spokespersons for the party. All party representatives are elected during the annual party convention.\n\n==Election results==\n[[File:MDG Valgvake 2013 (10024177254).jpg|thumb|The party's member of [[Parliament of Norway|Parliament]], [[Rasmus Hansson]], being interviewed by the [[Norwegian Broadcasting Corporation]] on the [[2013 Norwegian parliamentary election|2013 election night]]]]\n[[File:MDG Valgvake 2013 (10024221645).jpg|thumb|Former national spokeswoman [[Hanna Marcussen]]]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ [[Storting]] elections\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Date\n! colspan=\"3\"| Votes\n! colspan=\"2\"| Seats\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Position\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Size\n|-\n! #\n! %\n! \u00b1\n! \u00b1\n|-\n! [[1989 Norwegian parliamentary election|1989]]\n| 10,136\n| 0.4%\n| + 0.4\n| {{Composition bar|0|165|#67962e}}\n| {{steady}} 0\n| N/A\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 9th\n|-\n! [[1993 Norwegian parliamentary election|1993]]\n| 3,054\n| 0.1%\n| - 0.3\n| {{Composition bar|0|165|#67962e}}\n| {{steady}} 0\n| N/A\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 12th\n|-\n! [[1997 Norwegian parliamentary election|1997]]\n| 5,884\n| 0.2%\n| + 0.1\n| {{Composition bar|0|165|#67962e}}\n| {{steady}} 0\n| N/A\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 11th\n|-\n! [[2001 Norwegian parliamentary election|2001]]\n| 3,785\n| 0.2%\n| + 0.0\n| {{Composition bar|0|165|#67962e}}\n| {{steady}} 0\n| N/A\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 13th\n|-\n! [[2005 Norwegian parliamentary election|2005]]\n| 3,652\n| 0.1%\n| - 0.1\n| {{Composition bar|0|169|#67962e}}\n| {{steady}} 0\n| N/A\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 12th\n|-\n! [[2009 Norwegian parliamentary election|2009]]\n| 9,286\n| 0.3%\n| + 0.2\n| {{Composition bar|0|169|#67962e}}\n| {{steady}} 0\n| N/A\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 10th\n|-\n! [[2013 Norwegian parliamentary election|2013]]\n| 79,152\n| 2.8%\n| + 2.5\n| {{Composition bar|1|169|#67962e}}\n| {{increase}} 1\n| style=\"background:#fcc;\"| Opposition\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 8th\n|-\n! [[2017 Norwegian parliamentary election|2017]]\n| 94,427\n| 3.2%\n| + 0.4\n| {{Composition bar|1|169|#67962e}}\n| {{steady}} 0\n| style=\"background:#fcc;\"| Opposition\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 8th\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Green party]]\n* [[Green politics]]\n* [[List of environmental organizations]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Milj\u00f8partiet De Gr\u00f8nne}}\n*{{in lang|no}} [http://www.mdg.no/ Official site]\n\n{{Norwegian political parties}}\n{{Green parties}}\n\n[[Category:Green parties in Europe]]\n[[Category:1988 establishments in Norway]]\n[[Category:European Green Party]]\n[[Category:Environmental organisations based in Norway]]\n[[Category:Political parties established in 1988]]\n[[Category:Global Greens member parties]]\n[[Category:Political parties in Norway]]\n", "name_user": "Debatabletruth", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Green_Party_(Norway)"}
{"title_page": "Nabeel Qureshi (director)", "text_new": "{{about||the author|Nabeel Qureshi (author)||Nabeel}}\n{{Fanpov|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n|name          = Nabeel Qureshi\n|image         =\n|alt           = \n|caption       = \n|birth_date    = {{birth year and age|1985}}\n|birth_place   = [[Sukkur]], [[Sindh]], Pakistan\n|nationality   = Pakistani\n| occupation = {{flatlist|\n*Film director\n*screenwriter\n*\n}}\n|years_active  = 2004-present\n}}\n\n'''Nabeel Qureshi''' (born 1985) is an award-winning [[Pakistani]] film director, screenwriter and occasional singer best known for making movies that tackle socio economic issues in a thought provoking yet light hearted manner. Nabeel uses a unique style incorporated in his realistic stories, which in turn has gained a lot of critical acclaim. He made waves in Pakistani cinema with his debut feature film, ''[[Na Maloom Afraad]]'' (2014), where he won an award for best film director following up with his critical acclaimed and his biggest box office hit till date ''[[Actor in Law]]'' (2016), for which he again won an award for best director. His films topics probe the society to think about topics that are considered unimportant and don't matter in the system.\n\n== Early life ==\nQureshi was born in 1985 in [[Sukkur]], [[Sindh]] and moved to [[Karachi]] in 2004. he started his career from AAJ TV, where directed promos, after one year he left the job and started studying theatre at [[National Academy of Performing Arts]] (NAPA) and was dropped out because of some issues with the faculty in 2006.<ref name=Dec2014TN>{{cite news|last1=Ghafoor|first1=Usman|title=\u201cFilm is about story-telling\u201d|url=http://tns.thenews.com.pk/interview-nabeel-qureshi/#.VbRbmLOqqkr|accessdate=July 26, 2015|work=thenews.com.pk|date=December 28, 2014}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nQureshi started his career in mid-2000s by directing ads, cooking shows, television shows and television films.<ref name=Jan2015NLM>{{cite news|last1=Mahamadi|first1=Hiba|title=Undercover Director: Nabeel Qureshi|url=http://www.newslinemagazine.com/2015/01/undercover-director-profile-nabeel-qureshi/|accessdate=July 26, 2015|work=newslinemagazine.com|date=January 20, 2015}}</ref>\n\nQureshi is also the director of comedy news show ''[[Banana News Network]]'', which is being aired on [[Geo TV]] since 2011, it broadcasts every Wednesdays at 11:05 PM (PST).<ref name=\"Jan2015NLM\" /><ref>{{cite web|title=Banana News Network|url=http://www.geo.tv/geonews/program.asp?pid=1421|publisher=geo.tv|accessdate=July 26, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, Qureshi directed the music video of [[Mohsin Abbas Haider]]'s debut song ''Beparwah Dhola''.<ref>{{cite web|title=PakMusic Exclusive Audio/Video: Beparwah Dhola by Mohsin Abbas Haider|url=http://pakmusic.net/pakmusic-video-beparwah-dhola-by-mohsin-abbas-haider|publisher=pakmusic.net|accessdate=July 26, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Qureshi made his directorial debut with ''[[Na Maloom Afraad]]'', which he co-wrote with his college friend [[Fizza Ali Meerza]], who produced the film along with Mehdi Ali through her Filmwala Pictures.<ref name=\"Sep2014Dawn\" /><ref>{{cite news|last1=Muslim|first1=Samra|title=Cinema in Pakistan: What\u2019s Brewing?|url=http://www.thefridaytimes.com/tft/cinema-in-pakistan-whats-brewing/|accessdate=July 26, 2015|work=thefridaytimes.com|date=June 27, 2014}}</ref> The comedy thriller stars [[Fahad Mustafa]], [[Mohsin Abbas Haider]], and [[Urwa Hocane]], released domestically on October 6, 2014 by [[Hum Films]].<ref name=Sep2014Dawn>{{cite news|title=Na-Maloom Afraad set to hit screens on Eid-ul-Azha|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1130062/na-maloom-afraad-set-to-hit-screens-on-eid-ul-azha|accessdate=July 26, 2015|work=dawn.com|date=September 6, 2014}}</ref> The film became the box office hit in Pakistan and grossed \u20a812.2 crore until March 2015, with a budget of \u20a89 crore.<ref>{{cite news|title=Na Maloom Afraad is Pakistan's longest running film since 2007|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/857775/na-maloom-afraad-becomes-longest-running-film-since-2007/|accessdate=July 26, 2015|work=tribune.com.pk|date=March 23, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Syed|first1=Faria|title=Nabeel Qureshi talks 200 days of Namaloom Afrad|url=http://www.hipinpakistan.com/news/1146954|accessdate=July 26, 2015|work=hipinpakistan.com|date=April 24, 2015}}</ref> At the [[14th Lux Style Awards]], ''Na Maloom Afraad'' won the Best Film award, Nabeel went on to win the [[Lux Style Awards|Lux Style Award]] for Best Director and  Best Original Soundtrack for the lyrics of \"Billi\" for his film ''[[Na Maloom Afraad]]'', which he shared with Meerza. <ref name=\"Winners\" >{{cite web|title=Lux Style Awards 2015: \u2018Na Maloom Afraad\u2019 declared best film, Javaid Sheikh best actor and Ayeza Khan best TV actress|url=http://en.dailypakistan.com.pk/lifestyle/lux-style-awards-2015-na-maloom-afraad-declared-best-film-javaid-sheikh-best-actor-and-ayeza-khan-best-tv-actress/|publisher=[[Daily Times (Pakistan)|Daily Times]]|accessdate=October 1, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2015, Qureshi revealed that he and his writing partner Meerza were working on another project, later named ''[[Actor in Law]]'' which would be a social satire. <ref name=\"AIL\" >{{cite news|title=From the makers of 'Na Maloom Afraad' comes 'Actor in Law'|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/1026119/from-the-makers-of-na-maloom-afraad-comes-actor-in-law/|work=[[The Express Tribune]]|accessdate=14 January 2016|date=12 January 2016}}</ref> The first spell of the film was shot in Karachi in January 2016. <ref name=\"AIL\" /><ref>{{cite web| url=http://style360.tv/meet-greet-the-cast-of-actor-in-law/| title=Meet and Greet the cast of Actor in Law| work=Style360| accessdate=10 January 2016}}</ref> The film was released on the occasion of [[Eid al-Adha]] on September 9, 2016 to good response from the audience and went on to collect {{PKR|30 [[crore]]}} at the box office. <ref name=\"BoxOffice\">{{cite web|url=http://boxofficedetail.com/view_post.php?value=7422|title=Actor in Law \u2013 Box office record|website=Boxofficedetail.com|accessdate=25 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170729223054/http://boxofficedetail.com/view_post.php?value=7422|archive-date=29 July 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> \n\nAfter the success of ''Na Maloom Afraad'', the director-producer duo started thinking about a possible sequel of the film, and producer Fizza Ali Meerza said after nine months of the success of ''NMA'', in an interview with ''The Express Tribune'' that, \"We'd hopefully like to start working on a ''NMA'' sequel, but don't have a timeline in mind at present,\". \"We don't know if it's going to be a proper sequel or a spiritual successor through which we'll tell a different story this time\". <ref>{{cite news|title=Na Maloom Afraad to hit the road again|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/914888/n|date=4 July 2015|accessdate=23 June 2017|author=Hasan Ansari|work=The Express Tribune|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180730013616/https://tribune.com.pk/story/914888/n/|archive-date=30 July 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Filming began in March 2017 in Karachi, where few scenes were shot. <ref>{{cite news|title=Na Maloom Afraad 2 shooting begins|author=Adnan Majeed|url=https://trendsinpk.com/2017/03/17/na-maloom-afraad-2-shooting-begins/|date=17 March 2017|accessdate=23 June 2017|publisher=Trends in PK|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170828142749/https://trendsinpk.com/2017/03/17/na-maloom-afraad-2-shooting-begins/|archive-date=28 August 2017|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> while nearly the whole film was shot in Cape Town, [[South Africa]]. <ref name=\"trailerdawn\">{{cite news|title=Na Maloom Afraad 2 trailer is out now|author=Irfan ul Haq|url=https://images.dawn.com/news/1177864|date=22 June 2017|accessdate=23 June 2017|work=DAWN Images|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170622144136/https://images.dawn.com/news/1177864|archive-date=22 June 2017|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The film released on the festival of [[Eid al-Adha]], 2 September 2017 in Pakistan and worldwide. The film collected {{PKR|20 crore}} at the box office. <ref name=\"boxoffice\">{{cite news|date=7 October 2017|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1525333/p|author=Rahul Aijaz|title='Na Maloom Afraad 2' banned, previewed and cleared again in Punjab|work=The Express Tribune|accessdate=8 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nLater on he directed and co-wrote the social-comedy drama film ''[[Load Wedding]]'', starring [[Fahad Mustafa]] and [[Mehwish Hayat]]: which had released on 2018 [[Eid al-Adha]], and which earned critical acclaim as well worked in the box-office.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://gulfnews.com/1.2142835|title=Nabeel Qureshi promises fun with 'Load Wedding'|date=18 December 2018|accessdate=13 June 2018|work=[[Gulf News]]|author=Usman Ghafoor}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.pakistantoday.com.pk/2017/12/09/me|title=Mehwish Hayat, Fahad Mustafa to reunite in Load Wedding|work=[[Pakistan Today]]|accessdate=18 May 2018|date=9 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n=== Films ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Key\n| style=\"background:#ffc;\"| {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+\n|-\n! Year !! Film !! Director !! Writer !! Notes\n|-\n| 2014 || ''[[Na Maloom Afraad]]'' || {{yes}} || {{yes}} || \n|-\n| 2016 || ''[[Actor in Law]]'' || {{yes}} || {{yes}} || Special appearance in title song \"Actor in Law\"\n|-\n| 2017 || ''[[Na Maloom Afraad 2]]'' || {{yes}} || {{yes}} || \n|-\n| 2018 || ''[[Load Wedding]]'' || {{yes}} || {{yes}} || \n|-\n| 2020 ||''Quaid-e-Azam Zindabad'' {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}''|| {{yes}} || {{yes}} || Shoot is completed\n|- \n| 2020 ||''Fatman''{{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}''|| {{yes}} || {{yes}} || \n|}\n\n=== Frequent actor collaborations ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" width=100% style=\"text-align:left;\"\n|- style=\"vertical-align:top;\"\n! scope=\"col\" |<br />Actors\n! scope=\"col\" |<br />''[[Na Maloom Afraad]]'' <br />(2014)\n! scope=\"col\" |<br />''[[Actor in Law]]''<br />(2016)\n! scope=\"col\" |<br />''[[Na Maloom Afraad 2]]''<br />(2017)\n! scope=\"col\" |<br />''[[Load Wedding]]''<br />(2018)\n! scope=\"col\" |<br />Total\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"  style=\"text-align:left\"|[[Fahad Mustafa]]\n| {{ya}}\n| {{ya}}\n| {{ya}}\n| {{ya}}\n|4\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"  style=\"text-align:left\"| [[Mehwish Hayat]]\n| {{ya}}\n| {{ya}}\n| \n| {{ya}}\n|3\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"  style=\"text-align:left\"| [[Jawed Sheikh]]\n| {{ya}}\n| \n| {{ya}}\n| \n|2\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"  style=\"text-align:left\"| [[Mohsin Abbas Haider]]\n| {{ya}}\n| \n| {{ya}}\n| {{ya}}\n|3\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"  style=\"text-align:left\"| [[Hania Amir]]\n| \n| \n| {{ya}}\n| {{ya}}\n|2\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"  style=\"text-align:left\"| [[Urwa Hocane]]\n| {{ya}}\n| \n| {{ya}}\n| \n|2\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"  style=\"text-align:left\"| [[Nayyar Ejaz]]\n| {{ya}}\n| {{ya}}\n| {{ya}}\n| \n|3\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"  style=\"text-align:left\"| Irfan Motiwala\n| {{ya}}\n| {{ya}}\n| \n| \n|2\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"  style=\"text-align:left\"| Ashhad siddiqui\n| {{ya}}\n| {{ya}}\n| {{ya}}\n|\n|3\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"  style=\"text-align:left\"| Noor ul Hasan\n| \n| {{ya}}\n|\n| {{ya}}\n|2\n|-\n|}\n\n== Television ==\n=== TV ===\n* ''[[Banana News Network]]'' (Comedy TV show)\n\n=== As ads/music video director ===\n* ''Beparwah Dhola'' (2012), song by [[Mohsin Abbas Haider]]\n\n== Discography ==\n===Singles===\n* ''Khamosh Dono'' (2011)<ref>[http://www.pakium.pk/2011/02/14/nabeel-qureshi-khamosh-dono-official-music-video Nabeel Qureshi \u2013 Khamosh Dono (Official Music Video)], ''Pakium''</ref>\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Category\n! Nominated Work\n! Notes\n! Result\n! {{Abbr|Ref(s)|References}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 2015\n|rowspan=\"2\"| [[14th Lux Style Awards]]\n| Best Director\n| [[Na Maloom Afraad]]\n| \n| rowspan=\"3\" style=\"background: #99FF99; color: black; vertical-align: middle; text-align: center; \" class=\"yes table-yes2\"|Won\n|rowspan=\"2\"| <center><ref name=July2015Tribune>{{cite news|title=Lux Style Awards 2015 nominees announced|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/922031/lux-style-awards-2015-nominees-announced/|accessdate=July 26, 2015|work=tribune.com.pk|date=July 16, 2015}}</ref></center><ref name=\"Winners\" />\n|-\n| Best Original Soundtrack\n| \"Billi\"\n| shared with [[Fizza Ali Meerza]]\n|-\n| 2017\n| [[16th Lux Style Awards]]\n| Best Director\n| [[Actor in Law]]\n|\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.luxstyle.pk/lsa-moments/winners-list-and-pictures-of-16th-lux-style-awards-2017/|title=WINNER\u2019S LIST AND PICTURES OF 16TH LUX STYLE AWARDS 2017|work=[[Lux Style Awards]]|date=24 April 2017|accessdate=1 May 2017}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of film directors]]\n*[[List of Pakistani television directors]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|6567539}}\n{{authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Qureshi, Nabeel}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Sukkur District]]\n[[Category:Film directors from Karachi]]\n[[Category:Pakistani film directors]]\n[[Category:Pakistani television directors]]\n[[Category:Pakistani music video directors]]\n[[Category:Pakistani screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Pakistani male singers]]\n[[Category:Sindhi people]]\n[[Category:Writers from Karachi]]\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:National Academy of Performing Arts alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{about||the author|Nabeel Qureshi (author)||Nabeel}}\n{{Fanpov|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n|name          = Nabeel Qureshi\n|image         =\n|alt           = \n|caption       = \n|birth_date    = {{birth year and age|1985}}\n|birth_place   = [[Sukkur]], [[Sindh]], Pakistan\n|nationality   = Pakistani\n| occupation = {{flatlist|\n*Film director\n*screenwriter\n*\n}}\n|years_active  = 2004-present\n}}\n\n'''Nabeel Qureshi''' (born 1985) is an award-winning [[Pakistani]] film director, screenwriter and occasional singer best known for making movies that tackle socio economic issues in a thought provoking yet light hearted manner. Nabeel uses a unique style incorporated in his realistic stories, which in turn has gained a lot of critical acclaim. He made waves in Pakistani cinema with his debut feature film, ''[[Na Maloom Afraad]]'' (2014), where he won an award for best film director following up with his critical acclaimed and his biggest box office hit till date ''[[Actor in Law]]'' (2016), for which he again won an award for best director. His films topics probe the society to think about topics that are considered unimportant and don't matter in the system.\n\n== Early life ==\nQureshi was born in 1985 in [[Sukkur]], [[Sindh]] and moved to [[Karachi]] in 2004. he started his career from AAJ TV, where directed promos, after one year he left the job and started studying theatre at [[National Academy of Performing Arts]] (NAPA) and was dropped out because of some issues with the faculty in 2006.<ref name=Dec2014TN>{{cite news|last1=Ghafoor|first1=Usman|title=\u201cFilm is about story-telling\u201d|url=http://tns.thenews.com.pk/interview-nabeel-qureshi/#.VbRbmLOqqkr|accessdate=July 26, 2015|work=thenews.com.pk|date=December 28, 2014}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nQureshi started his career in mid-2000s by directing ads, cooking shows, television shows and television films.<ref name=Jan2015NLM>{{cite news|last1=Mahamadi|first1=Hiba|title=Undercover Director: Nabeel Qureshi|url=http://www.newslinemagazine.com/2015/01/undercover-director-profile-nabeel-qureshi/|accessdate=July 26, 2015|work=newslinemagazine.com|date=January 20, 2015}}</ref>\n\nQureshi is also the director of comedy news show ''[[Banana News Network]]'', which is being aired on [[Geo TV]] since 2011, it broadcasts every Wednesdays at 11:05 PM (PST).<ref name=\"Jan2015NLM\" /><ref>{{cite web|title=Banana News Network|url=http://www.geo.tv/geonews/program.asp?pid=1421|publisher=geo.tv|accessdate=July 26, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, Qureshi directed the music video of [[Mohsin Abbas Haider]]'s debut song ''Beparwah Dhola''.<ref>{{cite web|title=PakMusic Exclusive Audio/Video: Beparwah Dhola by Mohsin Abbas Haider|url=http://pakmusic.net/pakmusic-video-beparwah-dhola-by-mohsin-abbas-haider|publisher=pakmusic.net|accessdate=July 26, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Qureshi made his directorial debut with ''[[Na Maloom Afraad]]'', which he co-wrote with his college friend [[Fizza Ali Meerza]], who produced the film along with Mehdi Ali through her Filmwala Pictures.<ref name=\"Sep2014Dawn\" /><ref>{{cite news|last1=Muslim|first1=Samra|title=Cinema in Pakistan: What\u2019s Brewing?|url=http://www.thefridaytimes.com/tft/cinema-in-pakistan-whats-brewing/|accessdate=July 26, 2015|work=thefridaytimes.com|date=June 27, 2014}}</ref> The comedy thriller stars [[Fahad Mustafa]], [[Mohsin Abbas Haider]], and [[Urwa Hocane]], released domestically on October 6, 2014 by [[Hum Films]].<ref name=Sep2014Dawn>{{cite news|title=Na-Maloom Afraad set to hit screens on Eid-ul-Azha|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1130062/na-maloom-afraad-set-to-hit-screens-on-eid-ul-azha|accessdate=July 26, 2015|work=dawn.com|date=September 6, 2014}}</ref> The film became the box office hit in Pakistan and grossed \u20a812.2 crore until March 2015, with a budget of \u20a89 crore.<ref>{{cite news|title=Na Maloom Afraad is Pakistan's longest running film since 2007|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/857775/na-maloom-afraad-becomes-longest-running-film-since-2007/|accessdate=July 26, 2015|work=tribune.com.pk|date=March 23, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Syed|first1=Faria|title=Nabeel Qureshi talks 200 days of Namaloom Afrad|url=http://www.hipinpakistan.com/news/1146954|accessdate=July 26, 2015|work=hipinpakistan.com|date=April 24, 2015}}</ref> At the [[14th Lux Style Awards]], ''Na Maloom Afraad'' won the Best Film award, Nabeel went on to win the [[Lux Style Awards|Lux Style Award]] for Best Director and  Best Original Soundtrack for the lyrics of \"Billi\" for his film ''[[Na Maloom Afraad]]'', which he shared with Meerza. <ref name=\"Winners\" >{{cite web|title=Lux Style Awards 2015: \u2018Na Maloom Afraad\u2019 declared best film, Javaid Sheikh best actor and Ayeza Khan best TV actress|url=http://en.dailypakistan.com.pk/lifestyle/lux-style-awards-2015-na-maloom-afraad-declared-best-film-javaid-sheikh-best-actor-and-ayeza-khan-best-tv-actress/|publisher=[[Daily Times (Pakistan)|Daily Times]]|accessdate=October 1, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2015, Qureshi revealed that he and his writing partner Meerza were working on another project, later named ''[[Actor in Law]]'' which would be a social satire. <ref name=\"AIL\" >{{cite news|title=From the makers of 'Na Maloom Afraad' comes 'Actor in Law'|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/1026119/from-the-makers-of-na-maloom-afraad-comes-actor-in-law/|work=[[The Express Tribune]]|accessdate=14 January 2016|date=12 January 2016}}</ref> The first spell of the film was shot in Karachi in January 2016. <ref name=\"AIL\" /><ref>{{cite web| url=http://style360.tv/meet-greet-the-cast-of-actor-in-law/| title=Meet and Greet the cast of Actor in Law| work=Style360| accessdate=10 January 2016}}</ref> The film was released on the occasion of [[Eid al-Adha]] on September 9, 2016 to good response from the audience and went on to collect {{PKR|30 [[crore]]}} at the box office. <ref name=\"BoxOffice\">{{cite web|url=http://boxofficedetail.com/view_post.php?value=7422|title=Actor in Law \u2013 Box office record|website=Boxofficedetail.com|accessdate=25 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170729223054/http://boxofficedetail.com/view_post.php?value=7422|archive-date=29 July 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> \n\nAfter the success of ''Na Maloom Afraad'', the director-producer duo started thinking about a possible sequel of the film, and producer Fizza Ali Meerza said after nine months of the success of ''NMA'', in an interview with ''The Express Tribune'' that, \"We'd hopefully like to start working on a ''NMA'' sequel, but don't have a timeline in mind at present,\". \"We don't know if it's going to be a proper sequel or a spiritual successor through which we'll tell a different story this time\". <ref>{{cite news|title=Na Maloom Afraad to hit the road again|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/914888/n|date=4 July 2015|accessdate=23 June 2017|author=Hasan Ansari|work=The Express Tribune|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180730013616/https://tribune.com.pk/story/914888/n/|archive-date=30 July 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Filming began in March 2017 in Karachi, where few scenes were shot. <ref>{{cite news|title=Na Maloom Afraad 2 shooting begins|author=Adnan Majeed|url=https://trendsinpk.com/2017/03/17/na-maloom-afraad-2-shooting-begins/|date=17 March 2017|accessdate=23 June 2017|publisher=Trends in PK|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170828142749/https://trendsinpk.com/2017/03/17/na-maloom-afraad-2-shooting-begins/|archive-date=28 August 2017|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> while nearly the whole film was shot in Cape Town, [[South Africa]]. <ref name=\"trailerdawn\">{{cite news|title=Na Maloom Afraad 2 trailer is out now|author=Irfan ul Haq|url=https://images.dawn.com/news/1177864|date=22 June 2017|accessdate=23 June 2017|work=DAWN Images|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170622144136/https://images.dawn.com/news/1177864|archive-date=22 June 2017|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The film released on the festival of [[Eid al-Adha]], 2 September 2017 in Pakistan and worldwide. The film collected {{PKR|20 crore}} at the box office. <ref name=\"boxoffice\">{{cite news|date=7 October 2017|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1525333/p|author=Rahul Aijaz|title='Na Maloom Afraad 2' banned, previewed and cleared again in Punjab|work=The Express Tribune|accessdate=8 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nLater on he directed and co-wrote the social-comedy drama film ''[[Load Wedding]]'', starring [[Fahad Mustafa]] and [[Mehwish Hayat]]: which had released on 2018 [[Eid al-Adha]], and which earned critical acclaim as well worked in the box-office.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://gulfnews.com/1.2142835|title=Nabeel Qureshi promises fun with 'Load Wedding'|date=18 December 2018|accessdate=13 June 2018|work=[[Gulf News]]|author=Usman Ghafoor}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.pakistantoday.com.pk/2017/12/09/me|title=Mehwish Hayat, Fahad Mustafa to reunite in Load Wedding|work=[[Pakistan Today]]|accessdate=18 May 2018|date=9 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n=== Films ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Key\n| style=\"background:#ffc;\"| {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+\n|-\n! Year !! Film !! Director !! Writer !! Notes\n|-\n| 2014 || ''[[Na Maloom Afraad]]'' || {{yes}} || {{yes}} || \n|-\n| 2016 || ''[[Actor in Law]]'' || {{yes}} || {{yes}} || Special appearance in title song \"Actor in Law\"\n|-\n| 2017 || ''[[Na Maloom Afraad 2]]'' || {{yes}} || {{yes}} || \n|-\n| 2018 || ''[[Load Wedding]]'' || {{yes}} || {{yes}} || \n|-\n| 2020 ||''Quaid-e-Azam Zindabad'' {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}''|| {{yes}} || {{yes}} ||\n|- \n| 2020 ||''Fatman''{{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}''|| {{yes}} || {{yes}} || \n|}\n\n=== Frequent actor collaborations ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" width=100% style=\"text-align:left;\"\n|- style=\"vertical-align:top;\"\n! scope=\"col\" |<br />Actors\n! scope=\"col\" |<br />''[[Na Maloom Afraad]]'' <br />(2014)\n! scope=\"col\" |<br />''[[Actor in Law]]''<br />(2016)\n! scope=\"col\" |<br />''[[Na Maloom Afraad 2]]''<br />(2017)\n! scope=\"col\" |<br />''[[Load Wedding]]''